reviewText: My kids love this movie, age 3.5 and 13 months. Every year we DVR this movie and watch it I don't know, 2 times a day for a month. Well, not anymore!! Now we can watch it whenever we want. In fact it just traveled to Mexico with us and still hasn't gotten worn out. Who doesn't love a little story that secretly teaches kids that it's not only OK to be different, but it's really an awesome special thing also that needs to be celebrated. And let's not forget the songs, even I find myself singing them when heading down the hall, and the boys just LOVE when we all three start belting them out. YIPPY for Spookley!!
summary: we don't have to wait for halloween anymore...

reviewText: We taped this 2 years ago from the TV and recently purchased the DVD as our VHS tape was about to wear out!!! I had forgooten about Spookley at first but my then 2 year old daughter remembered it, asked for it by name and even recalled which VHS tape I'd recorded it on!!! Since then (2 years, my daughter is now 4 years oild) Spookley is a regular in our household! It really is a cute story with a good moral and catchy songs. The animation is very well done also....WE LOVE SPOOKLEY!!!!
summary: We love Spookley all year long!!!

reviewText: My kids love this DVD. Spookley is a pumpkin who is teased because he is different but this show teaches not to judge a book by it's cover. 5 Cute songs and it teaches a valuable lesson. Special features include:-Direct Play DVD-full screen version-Read Along with Bobby(Monster Mash) PickettMy 2 year & 8 year old love this show and ask for it all through the year.
summary: Entertaining show with a good message

reviewText: While this is no It's the Great Pumpkin,Chalie Brown it is a cute show for young kids.I bought it for my 4 year old granddaughter.She does watch it but is not as thrilled about it as I thought she would be.It does send a message about accepting others even thought they may be different from you(a square pumpkin in this case)It features some very different characters such as 2 cute bats named Bella and Boris and three talking spiders named Edgar,Allen and Poe.And of course several talking pumpkins and a walking.talking scarecrow(think Wizard of Oz).
